# High-Performance Game Server Architecture Implementation Plan

This plan details the implementation of a Clash Of Kings style distributed game server using Java 21 and Pekko 1.0.x with a "No-Ask" Command-Query and Mirroring pattern. 

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The directory `/home/rovshan/videos/conquerer-2` is currently empty.
> I will initialize a new Maven project using Java 21. **If you prefer Gradle or a specific package naming convention, please let me know.** Otherwise, I will default to Maven and `com.conquerer.server`.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Initialization

#### [NEW] `pom.xml`
Create the base Maven project configuration, explicitly adding Java 21 properties and dependencies for `pekko-actor-typed`, `pekko-cluster-sharding-typed`, `pekko-persistence-typed`, and PostgreSQL jdbc drivers.

#### [NEW] `src/main/resources/application.conf`
Configure Pekko Cluster, Serialization (Jackson), and Persistence layer.

### Core Architecture & Domain Models

#### [NEW] `src/main/java/com/conquerer/server/domain/models/PlayerProfileAggregate.java`
Contains all the mirrored info for a player, including `Progression`, `Resources`, and `BuildingMirror`.

#### [NEW] `src/main/java/com/conquerer/server/domain/models/BuildingState.java`
Contains the true state managed by `BuildingActor`.

### Messaging Protocols

#### [NEW] `src/main/java/com/conquerer/server/domain/protocol/Protocol.java` (Or separate components)
Contains the marker interface `JsonSerializable` and all inner `Command` and `Event` classes (e.g. `UpgradeBuildingCmd`, `StartConstructionCmd`, `BuildingUpdateNotification`, etc.).

### Domain Services

#### [NEW] `src/main/java/com/conquerer/server/domain/service/BuildingDomainService.java`
Pure functions for operations like cost calculation and validation.

### Actors (Master and Slave)

#### [NEW] `src/main/java/com/conquerer/server/actor/KingdomPlayerActor.java`
Implements the Master Actor with State Mirroring, firing `tell` commands to `BuildingActor` instead of using `ask`.

#### [NEW] `src/main/java/com/conquerer/server/actor/BuildingActor.java`
Implements the Slave Actor that handles real construction state ownership and replies to the Master upon successful persistence.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
*Currently no automated test structure since it's an empty proj.*

### Manual Verification
- We will start the Main application to verify the cluster forms locally.
- We'll write a simple bootstrap logic (`Main.java`) that simulates a client sending an `UpgradeBuildingCmd` to the `KingdomPlayerActor` Shard Region.
- We will observe the terminal output and logs to trace the internal "Push-based Update" flow:
  1. Master validates and forwards.
  2. Slave persists building.
  3. Slave notifies Master via callback.
  4. Master persists updated profile.
